<P>> #1 -pvp's can't do anything to pvp players, read the faq.

<BR>&gt; #2 Turning it on and then having it on for a few hours is WAY to
<BR>&gt; exploitable, thats not an option.
<BR>&gt; #3 If you only want to fight for periods that you choose then
<BR>&gt; have a guild war. They will be in the game.
<P>&gt; First, I think pvp- players must not be able to steal, heal or
<P>I do know that the pvp- players can’t help/heal pvp+ in EQ, I am just saying that it should always stay the same since it sure prevents cheating like it was in UO :)
<BR>As for my other suggestion, I think it is a good compromise providing it is implemented properly to avoid any possible exploitation. I.e. use of an advance warning system or a grace period before & after turning on/off the pvp switch & etc.
<BR>After all PKing is not exactly the same as guild wars/pvp actions since it needs to be neither an organized event nor so evident to both sides, what so ever.
<BR>
